name: Department of Veterans Affairs (VA)
description: A federal agency responsible for providing benefits and services to veterans.

name: Military Pay Benefits
description: A program providing financial assistance to eligible military personnel and their families.

name: Veterans Health Benefits
description: A program providing medical benefits and services to eligible veterans.

name: VA Healthcare Access Network (VAN)
description: A program providing healthcare access for rural veterans.

name: Veterans' Employment and Training Service (VETS)
description: A program providing employment services to eligible veterans.

name: Transition Assistance Program (TAP)
description: A program providing transition assistance to military service members preparing for separation or retirement.

name: Education Benefits
description: A program providing education benefits to eligible veterans and their families.

name: Home Loan Guaranty
description: A program providing home loan guaranty to eligible veterans.

name: Housing and Urban Development (HUD) VA Supportive Housing Program
description: A program providing housing support to homeless veterans.

name: Veterans' Preference
description: A program providing preference in hiring for certain federal jobs to eligible veterans.

name: Survivor Benefit Plan (SBP)
description: A program providing financial assistance to the surviving spouse of an eligible veteran.

name: Dependents' Educational Assistance (DEA) Program
description: A program providing education benefits to eligible dependents of military service members.

name: Health Care for Women Veterans (HCWW) Program
description: A program providing health care benefits to eligible female veterans.

name: Veterans' Employment and Training Service (VETS)
description: A program providing employment services to eligible veterans.

name: Transition Assistance Program (TAP) - VET TEC
description: A program providing transition assistance and vocational training to military service members preparing for separation or retirement.
